elements.text:
Blessed is You O Lord God, King of heaven and earth. Since the beginning your Spirit moved over the waters, You created the heaven and the earth. You made water the symbol of our regeneration, through it we participate in the death and resurrection of Your Son Jesus Christ our Lord. With joy and obedience to your command we make disciples of all nations, baptizing them in the Name of the Father, and of the Son and of the Holy Spirit, to grant new life unto all who shall be baptized in this baptismal font which we this day consecrate. O God, we praise and exalt and worship You through Your Son Jesus Christ our Lord in the Unity of the Holy Spirit, world without end. Amen.
We shall consecrate this pulpit unto the Lord by reading from the Gospel of Luke 6:47-49
Thereafter shall lay his hand on the pulpit saying;
